        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "ngKTE",
          "name": "Notes",
          "width": "fill_container",
          "fill": "$c:--card",
          "cornerRadius": 8,
          "stroke": "$c:--border",
          "strokeWidth": 1,
          "strokeAlignment": "inner",
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 8,
          "padding": 16,
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "udV08",
              "fill": "$c:--foreground",
              "content": "Implementation notes",
              "fontFamily": "$c:--font-secondary",
              "fontSize": 14,
              "fontWeight": "600"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "bJkgC",
              "fill": "$c:--muted-foreground",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "• Tabs are capability-driven: Console is hidden when the template declares no live console (consoleMode none / no RCON); Logs is hidden when the game logs only to stdout (no logPath). If the active tab disappears once the template resolves, the page falls back to Overview.\n• Quick actions = spec.capabilities.actions. No-param actions run on click; actions with params or confirm: true open the typed dialog (string / int / enum / bool). Client-side validation mirrors the agent: required fields, whole numbers for int, no control characters. POST /servers/{name}/actions/run, gated to operator+ — buttons render disabled for viewers. Actions with danger: true render icon + label in destructive red, and the dialog's Run button turns destructive.\n• Game status = spec.capabilities.status.metrics, read from GET /servers/{name}/status every 10s while running. Declared metrics keep the layout stable: value shows — until the first reading and offline when the server is stopped. The card is hidden when the template declares no metrics or has no RCON.\n• The run result banner (raw console output, truncated to 200 chars, dismissible) pins above the actions list; errors use the destructive variant. Templates without a console show the muted hint instead.\n• The server icon tints from spec.accentColor (minecraft #5B9A3E, valheim #D99A2B, terraria #4A90D9), falling back to the legacy per-game palette.",
              "lineHeight": 1.5,
              "fontFamily": "$c:--font-secondary",
              "fontSize": 12,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
